++ [[span class="dhl"]]Object Class[[/span]] Pending



++ [[span class="dhl"]]Special Containment Procedures[[/span]]



The full current layout of SCP-7719 is to be determined and recorded. Special Containment Procedures will be updated if containment challenges arise.



++ [[span class="dhl"]]Description[[/span]]



SCP-7719 is SCP Foundation Site+19[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Unknown relation to [[[scp-7001|Site-19]]].[[/span]], an underground facility of unknown origin and location. Architecture and interior decoration are in line with Department of Design's parameters for compact sites, save the substandard lighting system.



SCP-7719 continually expands at an indeterminate rate. As of writing, SCP-7719 has four underground floors.



++ [[span class="dhl"]]Addendum[[/span]] 7719.1



Each floor contains from two to four rooms of various utilities. The following is a list of the rooms on each floor and description thereof, as well as its contents, if possible.



-----



+++ Floor B4



[[div class="blockquote"]]

**Room Two**



A standard Foundation conference room. Several bloody right handprints are strewn across the walls. All members of the Overseer Council (excluding O5-13) are seated in the room. 

[[/div]]



[[div class="blockquote"]]

**Room One**



A standard Foundation conference room. Shattered pieces of metallic and red crystalline materials are laid on the table.

[[/div]]



-----



+++ Floor B3



[[div class="blockquote"]]

**Room Three**



A large storage room[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Room size noticeably exceeds external physical dimensions.[[/span]] containing various miscellaneous items, such as a bronze humanoid statue, several pink plastic lawn flamingos, an oily mass of flesh, among others.

[[/div]]



[[div class="blockquote"]]

**Room Two**



A manager office room belonging to Ronald Stimson, as written on the name plate. There is no indication of the office ever having been occupied or used.

[[/div]]



[[div class="blockquote"]]

**Room One**



An empty, charred room. Entering it inflicts a slight feeling of wanderlust.

[[/div]]



-----



+++ Floor B2



All four rooms are densely packed with coffins[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Faint smells of sulfur are noted.[[/span]] and can not be entered. Signs on the doors read "Disposal Joint currently at capacity. Refer to Mount Qomolangma Long-term Storage Facility."



-----



+++ Floor B1



[[div class="blockquote"]]

**Room Two**

A display room, showcasing a scale model of Prototype Site-19/█████████ ████████████████ Research Facility. Several  cabinets line the far wall, containing empty casefiles belonging to "Lieutenant M."

[[/div]]



[[div class="blockquote"]]

**Room One**



A studio filled with various supplies and miscellaneous items, such as spray paint, concrete mix, blueprints and blank HMCL ID cards. At the center of the room rests a blank canvas with the word "SORRY" written on it.

[[/div]]



-----



+++ Ground Floor



The ground floor comprises a long tunnel, connecting the facility's entrance to the stairs leading below. The pipes and wirings on the overhang are affixed with small, metallic dodecahedron shells.



[[include <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/component:image-block">:scp-wiki:component:image-block</a>

